. There is convincing data showing that as mitochondria age mitochondrial DNA (mtDNA) accumulates mutations decreasing energy output. Protecting highly unsaturated mitochondrial membranes against oxidative stress also consumes an extraordinary amount of energy"--cProvided by publisher.  a44 0aAgingxGenetic aspects. 0aMitochondria. 0aOxidative stress. 0aOmega-3 fatty acidsxHealth aspects.1 aValentine, David L.,eauthor.403University of Alberta Accessuhttp://marc.crcnetbase.com/isbn/9781466594876z(Unlimited Concurrent Users)  hUAINzCRC  aInternet AccesswLCc1i6712201-1001lINTERNETmUAINTERNETrYsYtE-RESOURCEu10/27/2014xE-BOOKzCRC01ahttp://id.loc.gov/authorities/names/n2009065063bhttp://viaf.org/viaf/101392426